<p><a href="https://github.com/templerobotics/Lunabotics2024-RIO/tree/actuators" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Actuators Branch</a></p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2024-01-31T00:25:33.271Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":46,"readers_count":45,"score":9.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":452699,"topic_slug":"bms-networktables-shuffleboard","display_username":"Jared","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/templerobotics/Lunabotics2024-RIO/tree/actuators","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - templerobotics/Lunabotics2024-RIO at actuators","clicks":3}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":9105,"username":"Fletch1373","name":"Fletch","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/fletch1373/{size}/220073_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":62764,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/bms-networktables-shuffleboard/452699/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3298372,"name":"Sam Carlberg","username":"SamCarlberg","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/samcarlberg/{size}/207684_2.png","created_at":"2024-01-31T01:12:11.265Z","cooked":"<p>You need to instantiate the BMS subsystem in your robot container. It’ll automatically be registered with the command scheduler to call the <code>periodic()</code> function.</p>
<p>Also, working with the network table entries directly isn’t necessary if all you’re doing is pushing data. You can use <a href="https://github.wpilib.org/allwpilib/docs/release/java/edu/wpi/first/wpilibj/shuffleboard/ShuffleboardTab.html#addDouble(java.lang.String,java.util.function.DoubleSupplier)" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">ShuffleboardTab#addDouble</a> and pass in a supplier, which can read from a cached field instead of from the serial port. (This has the added bonus of letting you read that same cached data somewhere else if you need it, without having to do another serial read).</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">private double[] m_voltages = new double[12];

@Override
public void periodic() {
  m_voltages = Arrays.stream(arduinoBMS.readString().trim().split("\\s+")).mapToDouble(Double::parseDouble).toArray();
}

private void createDashBoardData() {
  for (int i = 1; i &lt;= 12; i++) {
    String cellLabel = "Cell " + i + " Voltage";
    Shuffleboard.getTab("BMS")
      .addDouble(cellLabel, () -&gt; m_voltages[i])
      .withSize(1, 1)
      .withPosition((i - 1) % 4, (i - 1) / 4);
  }
}
</code></pre>
<p>I’m assuming that these serial port reads are fast and won’t block for longer than a few milliseconds; if they take longer, consider using a <a href="https://github.wpilib.org/allwpilib/docs/release/java/edu/wpi/first/wpilibj/Notifier.html" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Notifier</a> thread to periodically read data from the serial port without blocking the main thread.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2024-01-31T01:12:11.265Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":42,"readers_count":41,"score":13.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":452699,"topic_slug":"bms-networktables-shuffleboard","display_username":"Sam Carlberg","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.wpilib.org/allwpilib/docs/release/java/edu/wpi/first/wpilibj/Notifier.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Notifier (WPILib API 2024.2.1)","clicks":2},{"url":"https://github.wpilib.org/allwpilib/docs/release/java/edu/wpi/first/wpilibj/shuffleboard/ShuffleboardTab.html#addDouble(java.lang.String,java.util.function.DoubleSupplier)","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"ShuffleboardTab (WPILib API 2024.2.1)","clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":25916,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2084 Lead Mentor | WPILib Developer"},"post_url":"/t/bms-networktables-shuffleboard/452699/4","custom_user_title":"2084 Lead Mentor | WPILib Developer","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,